==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sumerian
<hw>Su*me"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Sumirian</asp>.]</altsp> <def>Of or pertaining to the region of
lower Babylonia, which was anciently called <xex>Sumer</xex>, or its
inhabitants or their language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sumerian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sumerian
<hw>Su*me"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Sumirian</asp>.]</altsp> <def>A native of lower Babylonia,
anciently called Sumer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sumless</ent>⟦br⟧
